Items.description: Ryan Zimmerman hit a tiebreaking homer off Peter Moylan with two outs in the ninth inning, and the Washington Nationals beat the Atlanta Braves 3-2 Sunday night in the first regular-season game at the $611 million stadium.
Items.title: Nationals home opener
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Final home opener at Yankee Stadium postponed until Tuesday because of rain
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Toronto Blue Jays

Items.description: The $138 million Tigers opened with a thud. Tony Pena Jr. hit a two-out, tiebreaking single in the 11th inning and the Kansas City Royals held on to beat Detroit 5-4 in Monday's opener.
Items.title: Tigers home opener
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Brandon Webb pitched six innings and the light-hitting Diamondbacks piled up three solo homers in a 4-2 victory that dampened Dusty Baker's debut as Reds manager.
Items.title: Reds home opener
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Tony Gwynn hit a sacrifice fly in the 10th inning and the Brewers beat Chicago 4-3.
Items.title: Cubs home opener
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Casey Blake hit a three-run double in the eighth inning Monday to give the Indians a 10-8 season-opening win over the White Sox.
Items.title: Indians home opener
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description:
The Washington Nationals took their late-inning act on the road.

Nick Johnson's tiebreaking RBI double off Tom Gordon highlighted a five-run ninth inning and the Nationals beat the Philadelphia Phillies 11-6 Monday.
Items.title: Phillies home opener
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: James Shields pitched seven innings of five-hit ball, Eric Hinske homered and the Tampa Bay Rays coasted to a 6-2 victory over the Baltimore Orioles Monday.
Items.title: Orioles home opener
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Brad Penny allowed four hits over 6 2/3 innings in his first Opening Day start and the Dodgers roughed up Barry Zito for four runs en route to a 5-0 win over the Giants Monday.
Items.title: Dodgers home opener
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Johan Santana struck out eight in seven dominant innings, David Wright hit a three-run double and New York opened its season with a 7-2 win Monday over Florida.
Items.title: Marlins home opener
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. New York Mets

Items.description: The opener between the Rockies and St. Louis was postponed by rain in the third inning with the Cardinals leading 5-1 on a home run by Albert Pujols.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Adrian Beltre hit a go-ahead groundout in the sixth inning, Jose Lopez had a two-run double in the seventh and the Seattle Mariners beat the Texas Rangers 5-2 in Monday's opener.
Items.title: Mariners home opener
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Xavier Nady hit his second homer of the game, a three-run shot in the 12th inning, and the Pittsburgh Pirates overcame a horrific ninth to ruin Atlanta's home opener, winning 12-11 on Monday night.
Items.title: Braves home opener
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Carlos Gomez formally replaced Torii Hunter as the Twins' center fielder and raced around the bases, giving Livan Hernandez and the Twins enough offense to beat the Los Angeles Angels 3-2 Monday night with a snowstorm swirling outside the Metrodome.
Items.title: Twins home opener
Items.vs: Minnesota Twins vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Jake Peavy hit an RBI single and a sacrifice fly, and pitched seven innings of three-hit ball to lead the Padres to a 4-0 win over the Astros in a season opener on Monday night.
Items.title: Padres home opener
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Chien-Ming Wang shut down the Blue Jays for seven innings, making Joe Girardi a winner in his rain-delayed debut as Yankees manager and sending New York to a record-setting 3-2 victory Tuesday night.
Items.title: Yankees home opener
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Toronto Blue Jays

Items.description: Robert Andino's first career home run with two outs in the 10th inning gave the Marlins a 5-4 win over the Mets on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Vladimir Guerrero and Garret Anderson had six hits and five RBIs between them, and Jon Garland breezed through his first start for Los Angeles with a 9-1 victory over the Twins on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Minnesota Twins vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Troy Glaus' throwing error allowed the tying run to score and Jayson Nix walked with the bases loaded in a two-run eighth inning, helping the Rockies begin defense of their NL championship with a 2-1 victory on Tuesday night.
Items.title: Cardinals home opener
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Trevore Hoffman earned his 525th career save on Tuesday night, pitching the ninth inning in the Padres' 2-1 win over the Astros.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Dice-K struck out nine and didn't walk a batter Tuesday night, allowing two hits and one run over 6 2/3 innings as the Red Sox beat the Athletics 2-1 in Oakland's home opener.
Items.title: Athletics home opener
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Rafael Furcal scored from second on pinch hitter Delwyn Young's infield hit with two outs in the ninth inning, giving the Dodgers a 3-2 victory over the Giants on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Josh Hamilton hit a two-run homer in the ninth off All-Star closer J.J. Putz, sending the Texas Rangers to a 5-4 victory over the Mariners on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Brian Bannister allowed two singles in seven innings, combining on a three-hitter in the Royals' 4-0 victory over the Tigers.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Jeff Suppan held Chicago to two runs and six hits in in 6 1/3 innings, Rickie Weeks homered on the game's first pitch and Jason Kendall reached base five straight times to lead the Brewers over the Cubs 8-2.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Jon Lester pitched three-hit ball into the seventh inning and David Ortiz broke open a scoreless game with a two-run homer as the Red Sox beat the Athletics 5-0.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Mark Teixeira hit a two-run homer and Yunel Escobar added a three-run shot in Atlanta's seven-run eighth inning and the Braves beat the Pittsburgh Pirates 10-2 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Aubrey Huff drove in four runs to rally the Orioles past the Rays 9-6 in from of the smallest crowd in Camden Yards history.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: A.J. Burnett overpowered the Yankees on a nippy night in the Bronx and Vernon Wells hit a two-run homer off Mike Mussina in the Blue Jays' 5-2 victory.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Toronto Blue Jays

Items.description: Tim Redding took a one-hitter into the eighth inning and Ryan Zimmerman hit a solo homer to help the Washington Nationals stay unbeaten with a 1-0 victory over the Philadelphia Phillies on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Fausto Carmona pitched seven innings in his season debut and Grady Sizemore had three RBIs to lead the Indians to a 7-2 win over the White Sox.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Edwin Encarnacion hit a three-run homer in the bottom of the ninth Wednesday night to send the Cincinnati Reds to their first win under manager Dusty Baker, 6-5 over the Arizona Diamondbacks.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Ryan Church and David Wright each homered, Carlos Beltran had three doubles and the New York Mets pounded out 17 hits in a 13-0 rout of the Florida Marlins on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Joe Saunders threw eight shutout innings and Howie Kendrick came home on a wild pitch in the seventh to lead the Los Angeles Angels to a 1-0 victory over rookie Nick Blackburn and the Minnesota Twins on Wednesday.
Items.vs: Minnesota Twins vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: New St. Louis Cardinals center fielder Rick Ankiel had a game that would have made Jim Edmonds proud.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Lance Berkman hit a three-run homer off Trevor Hoffman with two outs in the ninth inning and the Houston Astros rallied for their first win of the season, 9-6 over the San Diego Padres on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: The bullpen committee forced upon the Mariners by J.J. Putz's injury is apparently going to include anyone -- including a starting pitcher.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Tim Lincecum made his season debut in relief and scored the go-ahead run on Randy Winn's sacrifice fly to help the San Francisco Giants beat the Los Angeles Dodgers 2-1 Wednesday night and avoid their first 0-3 start since 1984.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: John Danks didn't allow a hit until Casey Blake singled leading off the sixth inning and Joe Crede hit a tiebreaking home run off Jake Westbrook in the eighth to lead the Chicago White Sox over the Cleveland Indians 2-1 Thursday.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Johnny Cueto allowed nothing more than Justin Upton's solo homer in seven innings, striking out 10 in an overpowering debut while leading the Reds to a 3-2 victory over the Diamondbacks.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Zack Greinke allowed one run in seven innings, and Alex Gordon and Mark Teahen homered to lead the Kansas City Royals over the Detroit Tigers 4-1 Thursday for a season-opening three-game sweep.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Jesus Colome walked Jayson Werth to force in the winning run in the bottom of the 10th inning, giving the Philadelphia Phillies an 8-7 victory over the Washington Nationals on Thursday.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: In the final game of an emotional return to the Metrodome, Torii Hunter homered leading off the seventh inning to back a strong start from Ervin Santana and help the Los Angeles Angels beat Minnesota 5-4 on Thursday.
Items.vs: Minnesota Twins vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Brad Thompson had a career-high six strikeouts in 6 2/3 innings and added his first career RBI in the Cardinals' 3-0 victory over the Rockies.
